# Middleware Performance Refactor

## Purpose
Fix severe performance bottlenecks, memory leaks, and global state anti-patterns in the `backend/internal/middleware` package.

## Scope
- Refactor JWT extraction to happen once early in the middleware chain.
- Fix the `os.ReadDir` I/O bottleneck in `ArmedMiddleware`.
- Replace unbounded `lastIPs` map in `ip_hopping.go` with an LRU cache or Redis-backed cache.
- Remove DB writes from the rate-limiting critical path (`triggerMFA`).
- Remove global `penaltyBox` variables and replace with injected dependencies.
- Remove redundant JWT extraction logic from `mfarequired.go`, `ip_hopping.go`, and `rate_limit.go`.

## Context Files
- `backend/internal/middleware/*.go`
- `backend/main.go`
- `.routines/audit_backend`
- `.routines/correctness`
